  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Add your <strong>smoked streaky bacon </strong>to one side of a <strong>baking</strong> <strong>paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) and put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 4 min</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1707824524681-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1707824524681-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1707824524681-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1707824524681-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1707824524681-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the bacon is cooking, crack your <strong>egg[s]</strong> into a large bowl and add 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong>, <strong>half </strong>your<strong> ground cinnamon </strong>(save the rest for later!) and 2 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Whisk everything together until smooth – this is your <strong>French toast mix</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1707824532458-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1707824532458-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1707824532458-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1707824532458-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1707824532458-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>apple[s]</strong> finely (skin on), discarding the core</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1707824538568-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1707824538568-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1707824538568-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1707824538568-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1707824538568-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>After an initial 4 min, remove the tray[s] from the oven and add your <strong>pecan</strong> <strong>nuts</strong> and <strong>walnuts</strong> to the other side of the tray[s]</p><p>Drizzle the nuts with <strong>half</strong> your <strong>honey </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and sprinkle with the<strong> remaining</strong> <strong>ground</strong> <strong>cinnamon</strong>, give everything a good mix up and return the tray[s] to the oven for 8-11 min or until the bacon is golden and crispy and the nuts have caramelised</p><p>Tip: Watch the nuts like a hawk to make sure they don’t burn!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1707824546245-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1707824546245-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1707824546245-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1707824546245-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1707824546245-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dip your <strong>brioche halves</strong> into the<strong> French toast mix </strong>until it's been absorbed by the bread</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a small knob of <strong>butter </strong>and a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once melted, add the <strong>soaked brioche</strong> and cook for 3-4 min on each side or until golden and crisp – this is your<strong> French toast</strong></p><p>Tip: You may need to do this in batches!</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1707824555761-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1707824555761-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1707824555761-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1707824555761-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1707824555761-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once melted, add the <strong>sliced apple</strong> with 1 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 1/2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until softened and caramelised</p><p>Tip: Watch these like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
